node.text:
It was so much fun hanging out all afternoon with the lovely Amy and Jean Pasquet @cognacpasquet where we wandered through their lush grapevine and toured their cellar, with old oak barrels sitting Cognac and Pineau des Charentes, before ending up here, in the tasting room. (I got a few sips of their new raspberry apéritif made from berries behind their family distillery and…wow💥was that good…) Their organic Pineau de Charentes is modern-tasting with vibrant, bright grape flavors with a lush background of young Cognac, especially the dark red rosé, and I was thrilled to meet them! (And am looking forward to making Jean’s mother’s Galette Charentaise, a recipe for buttery shortbread from the region, that Amy slipped me…😉)
.
#cognacpasquat #cognac #pineaudescharentes #galette #charentes

node.text:
This 25-year old Pineau de Charentes at @cognac_vallein_tercinier was so good I almost started crying. Pineau de Charentes, a blend of 2/3 grape juice and 1/3 Cognac is a favorite French apéritif. But the long aging gave it a very special finesse and a concentrated ripe apricot, vanilla, and pruneaux flavor. Catherine Tercinier of the family that makes Cognac and Pineau des Charentes said she sometimes uses a splash in a vinaigrette too(!)
.
#drinkingfrench #pineaudescharentes #cognac #madeingrance

node.text: Even though I was *just* in Marseille, my luggage was tightly packed, so happy to head to @welcomebio_bazar a great shop in Paris selling everything #écoresponsable - from glassware and housewares, to cookware and chocolate. They have a stellar selection of @lacorvette_marseille savon (soap) de Marseille made with olive oil, as well as copeaux (shards) to make your own laundry detergent with. I restocked my soap supply with the help of the super-charming and friendly staff. (The glassware is lovely, and affordable, but I’m pretty well-stocked in that department…😁)
